webpackJsonp([0xce12157b0ce1],{1807:function(e,a){e.exports={data:{markdownRemark:{html:'<figure style="width: 400px" class="align-center">\n  \n  <a class="gatsby-resp-image-link" href="/static/hk-17ace195dcfc9c0bfa37431b514bdbac-13c16.png" style="display: block" target="_blank" rel="noopener">\n  \n  <span class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper" style="position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 652px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;">\n    <span class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image" style="padding-bottom: 100%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;">\n      <img class="gatsby-resp-image-image" style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;" alt="hk" title="" src="/static/hk-17ace195dcfc9c0bfa37431b514bdbac-13c16.png" srcset="/static/hk-17ace195dcfc9c0bfa37431b514bdbac-ee3f5.png 300w,\n/static/hk-17ace195dcfc9c0bfa37431b514bdbac-eece9.png 600w,\n/static/hk-17ace195dcfc9c0bfa37431b514bdbac-13c16.png 652w" sizes="(max-width: 652px) 100vw, 652px">\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    \n  <figcaption> </figcaption>\n</figure>\n<h2 id="span-stylecolorbrown-time-span"><a href="#span-stylecolorbrown-time-span" aria-hidden="true" class="anchor"><svg aria-hidden="true" height="16" version="1.1" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a><span style="color:brown"> Time </span></h2>\n<p>I made my trip in May (Mid-season Sale, items decreased slightly, about 30%). You can go on Jul, Aug, Dec, and Jan for the Final Sale, but I recommend to go in Dec when you can not only enjoy Christmas but also get the Final Sale, as well as having a pleasant weather. It usually rains in Jul or Aug. Check the weather before you flight to pack suitable clothes.</p>\n<h2 id="span-stylecolorslateblue-attractions-span"><a href="#span-stylecolorslateblue-attractions-span" aria-hidden="true" class="anchor"><svg aria-hidden="true" height="16" version="1.1" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a><span style="color:slateblue"> Attractions </span></h2>\n<p>I have visited these places: Disneyland, Ocean Park, Wong Tai Sin, Chi Lin - Nan Lian Garden, Peak Tram - The Peak, Tsim Sha Tsui Clock Tower, Avenue of Stars, Tsim Sha Tsui, Tai O Fishing Village, Ngong Ping, Citigate Tung Chung Outlet, Temple Market, Jade Market, Mid-levels Escalator (the longest outdoor escalator in the world),  HK3D Museum (at that time, there was One Piece 3D exhibition).</p>\n<p>See the review <a href="http://aquabubu.com/blog/travel/Hong-Kong-trip/" target="_blank">here</a>.</p>\n<h2 id="span-stylecolortomato-food-and-drink-span"><a href="#span-stylecolortomato-food-and-drink-span" aria-hidden="true" class="anchor"><svg aria-hidden="true" height="16" version="1.1" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a><span style="color:tomato"> Food and Drink </span></h2>\n<p>There is a website in Hong Kong called <a href="https://www.openrice.com/en/hongkong" target="_blank">OpenRice</a> that has all information about the restaurants, special dishes, pictures, prices, hours, instructions to go. Or, you can take a look at my <a href="http://aquabubu.com/blog/cuisine/Hong-Kong-food-trip/" target="_blank">post</a> of Hong Kong food that I\'ve tried.</p>\n<p>Hong Kong food is a combination between Chinese &#x26; Western cuisine, extremely delicious, extremely memorable. This is what impressed me most. I enjoyed the food at about 20 local famous restaurants and those restaurants that are voted by the local people were really good. </p>\n<p>People here eat a lot of meat and less vegetable. When you eat the noodle, if want to eat vegetables, you have to order it separately. You will be charged more but it’s big enough for two people.</p>\n<h2 id="span-stylecolorseagreen-transportation-span"><a href="#span-stylecolorseagreen-transportation-span" aria-hidden="true" class="anchor"><svg aria-hidden="true" height="16" version="1.1" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a><span style="color:seagreen"> Transportation </span></h2>\n<p>I mostly used MTR. There are also special vehicles to try such as electric bus running on the Ding Ding railroad, cruise ship through Star Perry Island (these two are mainly for fun and relax, the price is very cheap, about HK$3).</p>\n<h2 id="span-stylecolorcrimson-fee-span"><a href="#span-stylecolorcrimson-fee-span" aria-hidden="true" class="anchor"><svg aria-hidden="true" height="16" version="1.1" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a><span style="color:crimson"> Fee </span></h2>\n<p>The list below is the <strong>money that needed</strong> for this trip. Of course, it\'s different by person but you can take a look and consider it as a reference. And these are <strong>for 1 person only</strong>.</p>\n<p><strong>Airplane</strong>: depend on your airlines</p>\n<p><strong>Visa</strong>: depend on your country</p>\n<p><strong>Hotel</strong>: ~HK$961 (4 nights in a 4-star hotel)</p>\n<p><strong>Disneyland</strong>: ~HK$480</p>\n<p><strong>Ocean Park</strong>: ~HK$240</p>\n<p><strong>Ngong Ping</strong>: ~HK$172</p>\n<p><strong>3D Museum Tickets</strong>: ~HK$155</p>\n<p><strong>Transportation</strong> (MTR-bus-ferry-peak tram, airport express): ~HK$446</p>\n<p><strong>Eating, gifts, other spendings</strong>: ~HK$1100</p>',timeToRead:2,excerpt:" Time  I made my trip in May (Mid-season Sale, items decreased slightly, about 30%). You can go on Jul, Aug, Dec, and Jan for the Final Sale…",frontmatter:{title:"Hong Kong traveling tips",cover:"/images/hk.png",date:"2015/05/15",category:"Travel",tags:["Travel","hongkong-tips","travel-exspense","kinh-nghiem","hong-kong","chi-phi","an-uong","what-to-bring","chuan-bi-do"]},fields:{slug:"/en/Hong-Kong-traveling-tips/"}}},pathContext:{path:"/en/Hong-Kong-traveling-tips/",langKey:"en"}}}});
//# sourceMappingURL=path---en-hong-kong-traveling-tips-00bd30595cd73d59c0b9.js.map